You've done your bit. Go ahead. We'll close up.

26
00:05:53,180 --> 00:05:54,180
什么状况？
What is it?

27
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:55,440
枪伤
GSW.

28
00:05:56,770 --> 00:05:58,050
你竟然能让他活着
It's amazing you kept him alive.

29
00:05:58,190 --> 00:05:59,670
呼吸暂停 脑干检验失败
Apneic, failed the brain stem test...

30
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,110
呼吸暂停反射
And the apnea reflex test.

31
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:03,830
我应该找到问题了 帕默医师
I think I found the problem, doctor Palmer.

32
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:05,570
你把一颗子弹留在他头里
You left a bullet in his head.

33
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:07,420
谢谢 它打在延脑上
Thanks. It's impinging on the medulla.

34
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:09,870
我需要专家 尼克诊断脑死
I needed a specialist. Nic diagnosed brain death.

35
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:11,750
我觉得不太对劲
Something about that doesn't feel right to me.

36
00:06:11,780 --> 00:06:12,780
我们快过去
We have to run.

37
00:06:14,330 --> 00:06:15,330
魏医师
Doctor west.

38
00:06:15,580 --> 00:06:16,830
你在干嘛？
What are you doing? Hey.

39
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,330
摘除器官 他是捐赠者
Organ harvest. He's a donor.

40
00:06:18,790 --> 00:06:20,180
先别急 我没有同意
Slow down. I did not agree to that.

41
00:06:20,210 --> 00:06:22,190
我不需要你同意 已经宣布脑死了
I don't need you to. We've already called brain death.

42
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:24,500
还有救 得帮他切除枕下颅骨
Prematurely.

43
00:06:22,966 --> 00:06:24,586
We need to get him prepped for sub-occipital craniotomy.

44
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:26,300
我不会让你帮死人开刀
Not gonna let you operate on a dead man.

45
00:06:26,590 --> 00:06:27,840
你看到什么？
What do you see?

46
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:29,890
- 子弹？ - 一颗完美的子弹
-A bullet? -A perfect bullet.

47
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:32,940
它经过硬化处理 铅锑合金可使子弹硬化
It's been hardened. You harden a bullet by alloying lead with antimony.

48
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:36,650
它是有毒金属 已直接溶入脊髓液
A toxic metal. And that's leeched directly into the cerebral spinal fluid.

49
00:06:36,890 --> 00:06:38,490
快速击中 中枢神经系统停摆
Rapid onset central nervous system shutdown.

50
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,520
我们该走了
We gotta go.

51
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:41,160
病人还没死 但有生命危险
The patient's not dead, but he is dying. Still want to harvest his organs?

52
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:42,610
还想摘他的器官吗？

53
00:06:43,690 --> 00:06:45,250
- 我协助你 - 不用
-I'll assist you. -No.

54
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:47,150
帕默医师会帮我
Doctor Palmer will assist me.

55
00:07:03,380 --> 00:07:04,970
谢谢
Thank you.

56
00:07:11,470 --> 00:07:13,220
手术影像导航 快
Image guidance, stat.

57
00:07:13,390 --> 00:07:14,890
来不及了
We don't have time for that.

58
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,680
你不能徒手进行
You can't do it freehand.

59
00:07:16,890 --> 00:07:18,020
可以 就这么办
I can and I will.

60
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:19,950
现在不是耍帅的时候 史传奇
This isn't a time for showing off, strange.

61
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,190
十分钟前
How about 10 minutes ago

62
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,860
你乱报死亡时间怎么说？
when you called the wrong time of death?

63
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,420
脑神经完整无损
Cranial nerves intact.

64
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:01,730
魏医师 盖住你的手表
Doctor west, cover your watch.

65
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:47,120
你没必要在大家面前羞辱他
You know, you didn't have to humiliate him in front of everyone.

66
00:08:47,150 --> 00:08:48,710
我也没必要救他的病人
I didn't have to save his patient, either.

67
00:08:48,730 --> 00:08:51,450
但我有时就是手痒
But I sometimes just can't help myself.

68
00:08:51,530 --> 00:08:52,900
尼克是个好医生
Nic is a great doctor.

69
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:54,160
是你来找我的
You came to me.

70
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,670
对 我需要第二意见
Yeah, well, I needed a second opinion.

71
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:56,790
你已经有了第二意见
You had a second opinion. What you needed was a competent one.

72
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,310
你需要的是高手

73
00:08:58,370 --> 00:09:00,640
那你更该来当我的神经外科顾问
Well, all the more reason why you should be my neurosurgeon on call.

74
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:02,130
你可以救更多的人
You could make such a difference.

75
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,800
我不能在你的屠宰场工作
I can't work in your butcher shop.

76
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:06,180
我连接横切脊髓
I'm fusing transected spinal cords.

77
00:09:06,210 --> 00:09:08,440
刺激中枢神经系统的神经生成
I'm stimulating neurogenesis in the central nervous system.

78
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:10,810
这项研究未来能救成千上万的人
The work I'm doing is gonna save thousands for years to come.

79
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:13,260
在急诊室只能救被枪击的醉汉
In er, you get to save one drunk idiot with a gun.

80
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:14,390
你说得对
Yeah, you're right.

81
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:15,930
我们在急诊室只是救人
In er, we're only saving lives.

82
00:09:16,010 --> 00:09:19,560
没有名望 也没人来采访
There's no fame, there's no CNN interviews.

83
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:21,510
看来我只好将就用尼克了
I guess I'll just have to stick with nic.

84
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,650
等一下
Wait a minute. You're not... You guys aren't...

85
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,000
你没有…你们该不会…

86
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:25,310
什么？
What?

87
00:09:25,390 --> 00:09:28,150
炮友？抱歉 我以为我够含蓄了
Sleeping together? Sorry, I thought that was implicit in my disgust.

88
00:09:28,230 --> 00:09:29,780
一点也不含蓄
Explicit, actually.

89
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:32,110
我才不来办公室恋情那一套
No, I have a very strict rule against dating colleagues.

90
00:09:32,190 --> 00:09:33,190
是吗？
-Oh, really? -I call it the "strange policy."

91
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:34,420
这叫史传奇原则

92
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,990
赞 我的名字成了专有名词
Good, I'm glad something's named after me.

93
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:39,420
我发明了椎板切除术
I invented a laminectomy procedure.

94
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:42,390
却没人想叫它史传奇手术
And yet, somehow

95
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:42,367
no one seems to want to call it the "strange technique."

96
00:09:42,410 --> 00:09:43,910
那是我们一起发明的
We invented that technique.

97
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:46,500
总之 你的原则让我受宠若惊
Regardless, I'm very flattered by your policy.

98
00:09:48,370 --> 00:09:51,840
今晚我要在神经外科学会晚宴演讲
I'm talking tonight at a neurological society dinner.

99
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,260
跟我一起去吧
Come with me.

100
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:55,140
又是演讲约会？
Another speaking engagement?

101
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:56,220
真浪漫
So romantic.

102
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:58,280
你以前很喜欢陪我一起去的
You used to love coming to those things with me.

103
00:09:58,300 --> 00:09:59,580
我们玩得很开心
We had fun together.

104
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,310
不 是你很开心
No! You had fun.

105
00:10:01,390 --> 00:10:03,190
那与我们无关 重点在你身上
They weren't about us, they were about you.

106
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:05,350
重点不只在我
Not only about me.

107
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:08,440
史蒂芬 任何事的重点都在你身上
Stephen. Everything is about you.

108
00:10:09,060 --> 00:10:10,940
也许我们可以联名
Maybe we could hyphenate.

109
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:13,110
史传奇帕默手术
Strange-Palmer technique.

110
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:15,070
帕默史传奇
Palmer-strange.

111
