比利
Billy.

112
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:05,750
什么状况？
What have you got for me?

113
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:07,470
35岁空军上校
I've got a 35-year-old air force colonel...

114
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,370
穿着某种实验性盔甲时撞碎了脊椎
Crushed his lower spine in some kind of experimental armor.

115
00:11:10,460 --> 00:11:11,830
脊椎中间破裂
Mid-thoracic burst fracture.

116
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,380
我可以帮忙
Yeah, well I could help...

117
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:14,790
但别的医生也可以
But so could 50 other people.

118
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,300
帮我找值得花时间的病人
Find me something worth my time.

119
00:11:16,590 --> 00:11:19,760
68岁女性罹患晚期脑干胶质瘤
I have a 68-year-old female with an advanced brain stem glioma.

120
00:11:20,470 --> 00:11:22,590
你想破坏我的完美纪录吗？
Yeah, you want me to screw up my perfect record?

121
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:24,140
想得美
Definitely not.

122
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,540
不然22岁女性
How about a 22-year-old female...

123
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,870
脑中有电子植入装置控制精神分裂
With an electronic implant in her brain to control schizophrenia...

124
00:11:28,890 --> 00:11:30,110
遭到雷击
Struck by lightning?

125
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,730
听起来有点意思
That does sound interesting.

126
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,030
麻烦传给我…
Can you send me the...

127
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:36,950
收到了
Got it.

128
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,750
嘿
Hey.

129
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,550
没事 你会好起来的
It's okay. It's gonna be okay.

130
00:12:57,650 --> 00:12:59,570
他们做了什么？
What did they do?

131
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:03,040
他们出动直升机去救你
They rushed you in a chopper.

132
00:13:03,110 --> 00:13:05,210
不过花了一点时间才找到你
But it took a little while to find you.

133
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:09,450
你困在车子里 错过了神经受损的黄金救援时间
The golden hours for nerve damage went by while you were in the car.

134
00:13:09,530 --> 00:13:12,210
他们做了什么？
What did they do?

135
00:13:15,330 --> 00:13:18,080
骨头里装了11根不锈钢钉
11 stainless steel pins in the bones.

136
00:13:19,170 --> 00:13:21,140
多处韧带断裂
Multiple torn ligaments...

137
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:24,310
双手神经严重受损
Severe nerve damage in both hands.

138
00:13:25,590 --> 00:13:27,810
你在手术台上躺了11小时
You were on the table for 11 hours.

139
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:29,810
你看这些固定器
Look at these fixators.

140
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:33,400
谁都不可能做得更好
No one could have done better.

141
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:41,740
我可以做得更好
I could have done better.

142
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,350
不
No.

143
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:14,100
给你身体一些时间复原
Give your body time to heal.

144
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,520
你毁了我
You've ruined me.

145
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:20,080
我要多久才能…
-How long until I can take... -Doctor strange.

146
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:21,250
史传奇医师
Those tissues are still healing.

147
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:22,900
那些组织还在复原中

148
00:14:22,980 --> 00:14:24,030
那就加快速度
So, speed it up.

149
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,870
经由肱动脉将支架装在桡动脉里
Pass a stent down the brachial artery into the radial artery.

150
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:28,950
也许可以
It's possible.

151
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:33,000
昂贵的实验性手术 但有可能成功
Experimental and expensive, but possible.

152
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:35,000
只要有可能就好
All I need is possible.

153
00:14:58,560 --> 00:14:59,560
抬起来
Up.

154
00:15:01,020 --> 00:15:02,020
抬起来
Up.

155
00:15:02,650 --> 00:15:04,520
让我看到你有用力
Show me your strength.

156
00:15:09,990 --> 00:15:11,330
这样没用
This is useless.

157
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,580
才怪 你做得到
It's not useless, man. You can do this.

158
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:18,090
那回答我 大学毕业生
All right, answer me this, bachelor's degree.

159
00:15:18,330 --> 00:15:20,830
你知道谁神经受损这么严重
Have you ever known anyone with nerve damage this severe

160
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,510
做了复健
to do this...

161
00:15:22,670 --> 00:15:23,840
然后完全康复？
And actually recover?

162
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:25,470
有一个男的
One guy, yeah.

163
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:28,010
在工厂发生意外 背部受伤
Factory accident, broke his back...

164
00:15:28,090 --> 00:15:30,510
身体瘫痪 腿部萎缩
Paralyzed, his leg wasted away.

165
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,930
推轮椅造成肩膀疼痛
He had pain in his shoulder, from the wheelchair.

166
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:35,560
一周来三次
He came in three times a week. Then one day he stopped coming.

167
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:36,920
有一天就不来了

168
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:38,940
我以为他死了
I thought he was dead.

169
00:15:39,020 --> 00:15:41,110
几年后 他在街上跟我擦身而过
A few years later, he walked past me on the street.

170
00:15:41,350 --> 00:15:42,750
- 用走的？ - 对 用走的
-Walked? -Yeah, walked.

171
00:15:42,770 --> 00:15:45,650
鬼扯 拿他病历给我看
Bullshit. Show me his file.

172
00:15:45,980 --> 00:15:48,450
找病历要一点时间
It'll take me a while to pull the files from the archive.

173
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:50,950
不过为了让你这臭屁王心服口服
But if it proves your arrogant ass wrong...

174
00:15:51,530 --> 00:15:52,700
值得
Worth it.

175
00:16:07,710 --> 00:16:09,640
我拜读你所有的研究
I looked at all your research...

176
00:16:09,710 --> 00:16:11,930
看过你寄的论文
I read all the papers you've sent.

177
00:16:12,090 --> 00:16:13,810
那不可能成功的
It's not gonna work.

178
00:16:13,970 --> 00:16:15,530
我想你不明白…
I don't think you realize...

179
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:18,060
受损有多严重 是这样的…
How severe the damages are.

180
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:19,380
最好的办法都失败了
-Here's the thing... -The best have tried and failed.

181
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:22,150
我了解 听我说
I understand. Here's the thing.

182
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,360
你要我做的事不可能成功 史蒂芬
What you want from me is impossible, Stephen.

183
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:25,730
别这样
Come on.

184
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,570
我也得考虑自己的名声
I've got my own reputation to consider.

185
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:29,450
- 艾提安 等等 - 我爱莫能助
-Etienne, wait. No. -I can't help you.

186
00:16:29,690 --> 00:16:31,050
不 等一下
